div.p:
MS annotation by Krauss: 'Nr 511. Liste der Hölzer aus N. Holland | von Dr. F. v. Müller Aug. 1869', and in pencil 'mit aufbewahren!' [List of timbers from New Holland, from Dr F. von Mueller, August 1869] and [to be kept!]. MS dated to May 1869, since this is when the specimens were shipped (see below).. List of wood specimens
The list is in a clerk's hand with an added note by M at the end.

div.p:
Gesandt mit dem Schiffe Great Britain Anfangs Mai von hier an Mess Betham & Blackitt für Hr Prof. Studienrath
Krauss's correct rank was Oberstudienrath .
Krauss u Hr Prof u Forst Rath v. Nördlinger zu Hohenheim. Fracht bis London frei.

Sent by the ship Great Britain in early May from here to Messrs Betham & Blackitt
M's shipping agents in London. Great Britain sailed from Melbourne on 5 May 1869 (Argus, 6 May 1869, p. 4). for Professor Counsellor Krauss and Professor and Forestry Counsellor von Nördlinger at Hohenheim. Freight is free as far as London.
